-- layer-8 fixture: the dispatched `List` Functor `map` over a list large enough to
-- overflow V8's stack BEFORE the WasmGC impl-method TMC (Phase 2 B-dispatch) lands.
--
-- `map`'s impl is `map f (x::xs) = f x :: map f xs` — the self-call (`CMethod map
-- (RKey List)`) sits in cons-tail position, so without the destination-passing loop
-- the emitted `$mdk_impl_List_map` recurses via `call $mdk_impl_List_map` inside the
-- `struct.new $C_Cons` args → the frame stays live → a 2,000,000-element list overflows
-- (`Maximum call stack size exceeded`).  With wTrmcImplTry the impl is a constant-stack
-- loop (a `loop $tmcloop` / `br $tmcloop`, NO recursive `call`), so it runs.
--
-- `firstOf` is inlined (no `import list`) so the modules path sees only runtime+core; it
-- forces the WHOLE mapped spine (strict WasmGC list cells) then reads cell 0 WITHOUT a
-- `fold`/`length` (those are a SEPARATE accumulator-recursion TMC layer, out of scope).
firstOf : List Int -> Int
firstOf [] = 0
firstOf (x::_) = x

main = "head=" ++ intToString (firstOf (map (x => x * 2) [1..2000000]))
